I am Noam Avigdor, an engineer with over 30 years of technical and operational experience in the medical device industry and defense industry.&nbsp;

At&nbsp;Noam Med-Defense&nbsp;&nbsp;I provide end-to-end engineering support, specializing in Design Transfer&nbsp;Sustaining Engineering,&nbsp;and process optimization in stringent regulatory environments.

The core value I bring is a deep and uncompromising connection between Engineering, QA, RA and Manufacturing&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Instead of "throwing" recommendations from the outside

I dive into the details:&nbsp;&nbsp;BOM, drawings, ECOs, product files, manufacturing and testing processes. My approach is hands-on, based on field experience, and results-oriented.

I work with a true Risk-Based approach:&nbsp;

Focusing on what threatens regulatory approval, product quality or manufacturing stability, sharp distinction between Must and&nbsp;Nice to Have&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;and making decisions under time, budget and schedule constraints.&nbsp;

Over the years I have led process optimization around PLM systems, configuration management and engineering changes

As well as accelerating approval processes through parallel execution of Design Approval and Process Validation&nbsp;

My goal is simple:&nbsp;

To help organizations bring products to market faster, in a stable, practical and standards-compliant manner, while reducing risks and increasing operational maturity over time
